(2, 'Dentist', '$159,770 per year \r\n', 'Doctoral or professional degree', 'None', 'Dentists diagnose and treat problems with a patient\'s teeth, gums, and related parts of the mouth. They provide advice and instruction on taking care of the teeth and gums and on diet choices that affect oral health.'),
(3, 'Environmental Scientists and Specialists', '$68,910 per year \r\n', 'Bachelor\'s degree', 'None', 'Environmental scientists and specialists use their knowledge of the natural sciences to protect the environment and human health. They may clean up polluted areas, advise policymakers, or work with industry to reduce waste.'),
