(5, 'Biochemists and Biophysicists', '$82,180 per year \r\n', 'Doctoral or professional degree', 'None', 'Biochemists and biophysicists study the chemical and physical principles of living things and of biological processes, such as cell development, growth, heredity, and disease.'),
(6, 'Microbiologists', '$66,850 per year \r\n', 'Bachelor\'s degree', 'None', 'Microbiologists study microorganisms such as bacteria, viruses, algae, fungi, and some types of parasites. They try to understand how these organisms live, grow, and interact with their environments.'),
(7, 'Medical Scientist', '$80,530 per year \r\n', 'Doctoral or professional degree', 'None', 'Medical scientists conduct research aimed at improving overall human health. They often use clinical trials and other investigative methods to reach their findings.');

